snippet.textDisplay:
Sir, there seems to be a great ignorance all around on the language of the Pakistan's National Anthem which should have been morally  in the National language ie Urdu. The research shows that Jinha had requested an Indian friend to write the National Anthem of Pakistan which was in Urdu and easy to recite. Mr Ludhianavi wrote the same and the Anthem was sung till 1954 . 
However , by this  time Pakistan was desperately trying to distance itself from the Indian influence as the heritage of both the nations was common for centuries and maximum population  of Muslims was that of Hindus  converted to Islam as the Turk conquerers had already left with the loot. 
Urdu's birth was in India with the amalgamation  of Persian , Sanskrit and Hindi. The greatest scholars of present Urdu still reside in India. Pakistan ,in an effort to get closer to the Arabic Nations got the National Anthem re-written which with due humility is not in Urdu and rather difficult to remember for the young population since even the spoken Urdu in Pakistan has strong influence of Hindi, their parental  language. No wonder that the Children , as evident from a video on YouTube, find it extremely difficult to recite the same. The copy of Jan Gan Man (Indian National Anthem),as above,  has however been made well. Congratulations. Wishing you all a Happy Independence Day. Regards.
